the "SiteData" page for the "Home" menu item/link 

the following is the basic layout/wireframe/flow for the "SiteData" page/link 
 when the user selects the "SiteData" link from the main navBar
	-from the navBar, the user can select any of the other navBar menu/link items
	-user can also select the "upper right" login/registration/passwd items
		app logic will handle user based on user login status..



**SiteData
	Home	UserRoles	User -(System Actions)	Rewards/Referral(Actions)	SiteData	PartnerSites	AboutUs		SiteGuide (How To:)
																			  ViewColleges/~UserGoal/~UserSoFar -- by Area --prob better to 
																												do area, and list the colleges
																			  ViewBizPartners
																				-by Area --tgtBizType/byCount/byActualCount (ties into Rewards)





user selects the "SiteData" link/menuItem
 app displays the child links for the "different" types of "SiteData" for the site
	-"ViewColleges/User Data"	-users are able to view top level data for colleges in the system 
								 as well as rough user count (current/tgt)
	-"ViewBizPartners" 	--users are able to view top level data for local Biz/Ad Partners in the system 
								 as well as rough Biz count (current/tgt)



 all users are able to view the overall data

each link displays a section/content with basic explanation for the action/process, 
 and the "form/process" to handle the action/submit


 points the user to the "SiteGuide" menu item/link for more information about the 
	User-System Action processes


::ViewColleges/User Data
	selecting 'ViewColleges/User Data' allows user to select different attributes to 
	 get a feel for the Colleges/Users by area
	 -gives user/local Biz a feel for the scope of the size of the community
	 -useful for initial/rough thoughts on whether biz might want to advertise
	 -link would point local Biz to the BizPartner site for more granular 
	  information on the Bookstore/Local Biz/Ad Platform process 

	-app displays new/updated section using clientside javascript to mod the 
		client/frontside DOM
		changing "data" on the client/front with "submit" invokes ajax/async 
		 processes to send/fetch data between front/srvr.
		html changes occur on client/front with data from back
		faster process
		-uses base javascript or javascript libs...
	-decide if the action creates different page, or different space/area within 
		the current page

		 The Textbook platform is targeting a base number of Users
			to signup to test/use the platform, as well as a base number of 
			Local Companies to signup to test/advertise on the Platform.

			This page tracks/shows the number/data for these items during the 
			 initial prelaunch timeframe.

					Number of 	Number of		Number of
			date	Colleges 	Users (total)	Local Companies (total)

			1/1/1		222			33			44

			pull this tbl/data from the frontside user signin/email
			 as well as the collegeListTBL, and the bizCompany LandingPage
			 process/data



::ViewBizPartners
	selecting 'ViewBizPartners' allows user to select different attributes to 
	 get a feel for the scope of the Local Businesses/Ad Partners by area
	 -gives user/local Biz a feel for the scope of the size of the community/
	  Local Biz Community the process is driving towards
	 -useful for initial/rough thoughts on whether biz might want to advertise, 
	  or if students want to be SalesRep
	 -link would point local Biz to the BizPartner site for more granular 
	  information on the Bookstore/Local Biz/Ad Platform process
	 -link to point user for SalesRep-- to the SalesRep Site for more information 
	-app displays new/updated section using clientside javascript to mod the 
		client/frontside DOM
		changing "data" on the client/front with "submit" invokes ajax/async 
		 processes to send/fetch data between front/srvr.
		html changes occur on client/front with data from back
		faster process
		-uses base javascript or javascript libs...
	-decide if the action creates different page, or different space/area within 
		the current page

the "page"/layout of the page for this section/menuItem still has the main navBar, allowing the 
	user to then select the given menuItem from the main navBar






